timelogger

Class Task

  • java.lang.Object
    • timelogger.Task

  • public class Task
extends java.lang.Object
    With the instantiation of this class we can create tasks. We can set a tasks Id, the time of its start, the time of its end, we can add a comment to detail. We can check if a task Id is valid and we can ask for the duration of the task.

        This method is a constructor with the following parameters.
        Parameters:
        taskId - This is the Id of the task. Redmine project: 4 digits, LT project: LT-(4 digits)
        comment - In this parameter you can add some detail about what did you do exactly.
        startTime - You can set the time when you started the task: LocalTime.of(hh,mm)
        endTime - You can set the time when you finished the task: LocalTime.of(hh,mm)
